fields.name: Barrafina
fields.description: A bustling, Barcelona-style tapas restaurant and the original small-plates-and-no-reservations counter bar pioneer.

fields.name: Counter Culture
fields.description: A casual, creative and cool joint in Clapham - on a sunny day, the alfresco tables are a prime people-watching location.

fields.name: The Barbary
fields.description: A ‘modern Israeli’ small plates restaurant in the heart of Neal’s Yard, Covent Garden.

fields.name: Som Saa
fields.description: Thai street food in a stylish and exotic former garment factory walking distance from Liverpool Street.

fields.name: Hoppers
fields.description: A restaurant serving exclusively Sri Lankan dishes in the heart of Soho.

fields.name: Ceviche Soho
fields.description: A Latin dance party on your plate and in your glass!

fields.name: Bao
fields.description: A dinky Soho eatery serving fiery food you can eat with your fingers – and have time to queue.

fields.name: Rök Smokehouse and Bar
fields.description: A hip destination for thise who don’t want to have to compromise on food, cocktails, ambience or service.

fields.name: Social Eating House
fields.description: Informal but slick service and a big-ticket menu from Ramsay protégé and unstoppable wunderkind Jason Atherton.

fields.name: Roka
fields.description: It’s a popular spot for media schmoozing, but also suited to a special occasion when you don’t mind parting with a fair few pennies.
